# Library Directory

This directory is intended for project specific (private) libraries.
PlatformIO will compile them to static libraries and link them into the program.

The source code of each library should be placed in its own directory (e.g. lib/Firebase_ESP32/).

For example, see a structure for an existing library:

```
lib/Firebase_ESP32/
|-- src/
|   |-- Firebase.h
|   |-- Firebase.cpp
|-- README
```

For more examples and a guide how to create your own library, read the article:
https://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/lib/index.html#external-libraries
